 -- tCHAPTER 19. DOMINION TAX ADMINISTRATION INDIRECT TAXES -- tAPPENDIX -- tBIBLIOGRAPHY -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aTaxation in Canada remains the only volume to present under one cover a complete description of the Dominion, provincial, and municipal tax structure in Canada. The principal tax sources at the three levels of government are described briefly and readably, with enough detail to be of value to the student or expert but at the same time enough attention to broader aspects to be of interest to the general reader. In the description of the present Dominion taxes particular attention is devoted to the income tax, but there are also chapters on death duties, the tariff, the sales tax, and on the excise taxes and duties. Provincial taxes discussed in detail include corporation taxes, gasoline, sales and other consumption taxes, liquor and motor vehicle revenues, succession duties, and revenues from the public domain, including forestry and mining. Other chapters deal with municipal property tax and sources of local revenue. In each case the description covers the tax structure in Newfoundland. Of equal interest are also the chapters dealing with the enactment and administration of the tax laws.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aTaxationxLaw and legislationzCanada. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Taxation / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148758280740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487582807423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487582807.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LA